main event: A document from Project Blue Book concludes that unidentified flying objects reported were caused by the moon and time exposure effects.
interesting points: The object was identified as the unusually bright twin stars obscured by the moon., The photograph was taken during the evening of 20 March 1950, when a new moon rose., Analysts noted a streak of light typical of a moving ground vehicle in the photograph., The report was prepared for the United States Air Force by Battelle Memorial Institute and Rand Corporation., Harold E. Watson signed off the report as Chief of the Intelligence Department.
sighted object: an unidentified object in the sky
witness description: Photographic analysts and astronomers involved in the review.
